WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:01:41.280 --> 00:01:46.260
Candy, candy... sluggie-uggie!

3
00:01:43.240 --> 00:01:46.260
Wave Room

4
00:02:04.710 --> 00:02:09.140
What do you mean you're done for?!
What's happening over there?!

5
00:02:09.140 --> 00:02:11.070
Hey, guys!

6
00:02:11.070 --> 00:02:13.670
If we get caught in that wave,
we'll be done for!

7
00:02:13.670 --> 00:02:16.220
Oh right! We have the Coup de Burst!

8
00:02:17.510 --> 00:02:21.490
We can't use it!
We don't have enough cola!

9
00:02:21.490 --> 00:02:25.600
Pedro, I'm sorry!
You sacrificed yourself to save us, but...

10
00:02:42.390 --> 00:02:44.880
Everyone, listen!

11
00:02:46.100 --> 00:02:49.850
My cake!

12
00:02:55.280 --> 00:02:57.520
Wait! Wait, wait!

13
00:02:57.520 --> 00:03:00.230
Wait a minute, Mama!

14
00:03:00.230 --> 00:03:03.710
If you do that,
the cake will sink into the sea, too!

15
00:03:03.710 --> 00:03:06.090
Mama!

16
00:03:06.090 --> 00:03:06.850
Hurry up!

17
00:03:06.850 --> 00:03:07.730
Okay!

18
00:03:11.960 --> 00:03:15.260
D-Does this look okay, Jinbe-san?!

19
00:03:15.280 --> 00:03:18.200
Yes, that's fine!

20
00:03:18.200 --> 00:03:23.060
But it's too reckless!
You're trying to handle a ship's sails all on your own!

21
00:03:26.220 --> 00:03:28.360
Nami! How is the wind?!

22
00:03:29.860 --> 00:03:32.740
A strong wind is coming from the south!

23
00:03:33.230 --> 00:03:34.840
All right!

24
00:03:34.840 --> 00:03:37.070
What are you going to do, Jinbe?!

25
00:03:43.530 --> 00:03:46.100
I'm gonna tack this ship as fast as I can!

26
00:03:46.100 --> 00:03:47.600
What?!

27
00:03:47.600 --> 00:03:50.550
Are you joking?!
Why do you want to turn the ship?!

28
00:03:51.540 --> 00:03:54.270
We're going to enter the green room!

29
00:03:54.270 --> 00:03:57.510
Here we go! Here we go!

30
00:04:16.190 --> 00:04:18.870
The green room?! What's that?!

31
00:04:18.870 --> 00:04:22.700
Why are we heading toward the wave, Jinbe?!

32
00:04:25.220 --> 00:04:29.860
I see! This green room you're talking about
must be heaven!

33
00:04:29.960 --> 00:04:34.320
Doctor! I'll be heading over to your side soon!

34
00:04:36.280 --> 00:04:40.200
It's over! This is impossible!
We aren't surfing, you know!

35
00:04:41.570 --> 00:04:43.170
Pedro!

36
00:04:49.540 --> 00:04:53.010
Hold on tight to the ship!

37
00:04:55.420 --> 00:04:58.390
Splash!

38
00:05:07.020 --> 00:05:09.780
What's wrong?! What happened?!

39
00:05:16.070 --> 00:05:19.020
Hey, can you hear me?!

40
00:05:19.020 --> 00:05:22.290
Somebody! Say something!

41
00:05:25.370 --> 00:05:26.530
Huh?

42
00:05:28.780 --> 00:05:33.020
Is this heaven? It's beautiful...

43
00:05:33.020 --> 00:05:36.340
This is a good ship!

44
00:05:36.360 --> 00:05:42.340
The green room is found within surging waves.
It is a room of waves that forms for a brief moment.

45
00:05:42.970 --> 00:05:47.960
It has always been the perfect playground for fishman children!

46
00:05:47.960 --> 00:05:50.770
Then, this place is...

47
00:05:51.760 --> 00:05:54.730
...inside the wave?!

48
00:05:55.300 --> 00:05:58.010
We're gonna sail through it! Hang on!

49
00:06:12.120 --> 00:06:15.830
We have a good ship
and a good navigator!

50
00:06:15.830 --> 00:06:20.680
With a good helmsman,
this ship will be invincible!

51
00:06:20.680 --> 00:06:26.260
Amazing! He's controlling a sloop
like it's part of his own body!

52
00:06:26.500 --> 00:06:29.650
I've never seen such a helmsman before!

53
00:06:29.650 --> 00:06:32.970
You're amazing, Jinbe!

54
00:06:32.970 --> 00:06:35.930
So we're not gonna die?!

55
00:06:45.330 --> 00:06:50.130
Wedding...

56
00:06:53.460 --> 00:06:58.020
Oh well...
Serves you weaklings right!

57
00:06:58.020 --> 00:07:00.040
Lick!

58
00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:03.800
This is Perospero.

59
00:07:03.800 --> 00:07:05.300
Hey, Katakuri.

60
00:07:05.300 --> 00:07:08.520
We took care of all of them!

61
00:07:08.520 --> 00:07:09.920
What?!

62
00:07:09.920 --> 00:07:12.930
Hey, Nami! Brook! Carrot!

63
00:07:12.930 --> 00:07:14.510
Oh dear!

64
00:07:14.510 --> 00:07:17.890
We were just about to invade the ship!

65
00:07:17.890 --> 00:07:19.930
The plan's canceled, guys!

66
00:07:19.930 --> 00:07:24.450
It seems like the ship has already
sunk into the sea.

67
00:07:24.460 --> 00:07:27.400
But it's strange, Big Sis.

68
00:07:27.400 --> 00:07:30.960
The other side of the mirror
doesn't look like it's underwater.

69
00:07:32.210 --> 00:07:33.310
Look!

70
00:07:33.310 --> 00:07:35.620
No way!

71
00:07:35.620 --> 00:07:40.590
But, just to make sure,
shoot one more time.

72
00:07:43.840 --> 00:07:47.830
Wow! The mirror!
Big Sis, it suddenly broke!

73
00:07:47.830 --> 00:07:50.770
What? What? What's going on?!

74
00:07:58.290 --> 00:08:00.870
Nami-san !
Why did you break the mirror?!

75
00:08:00.870 --> 00:08:04.590
Luffy-san can't
come back to the ship without it!

76
00:08:05.170 --> 00:08:09.910
Let me focus just on this guy!

77
00:08:11.890 --> 00:08:16.810
Just break them all!
Every single mirror on the ship!

78
00:08:17.060 --> 00:08:18.040
But...

79
00:08:18.040 --> 00:08:20.980
Do you want to get in Luffy's way?!

80
00:08:23.520 --> 00:08:26.990
These are our captain's orders! Hurry up!

81
00:08:28.680 --> 00:08:30.590
There are still some mirrors!

82
00:08:32.770 --> 00:08:34.460
I found one, Joscar!

83
00:08:34.870 --> 00:08:37.220
I found it, too, Mascar!

84
00:08:40.770 --> 00:08:42.630
Let's do it, Joscar!

85
00:08:42.630 --> 00:08:44.600
Let's do it, Mascar!

86
00:08:45.360 --> 00:08:47.940
Make sure to find all the mirrors!

87
00:08:54.230 --> 00:08:55.610
Shoot!

88
00:09:11.170 --> 00:09:12.880
What?!

89
00:09:12.880 --> 00:09:14.890
What's going on?!

90
00:09:19.320 --> 00:09:20.840
This is the last one!

91
00:09:23.900 --> 00:09:26.260
Are those guys alive?

92
00:09:26.260 --> 00:09:29.750
Big Bro Peros said they took care of them...

93
00:09:29.750 --> 00:09:33.510
I guess the ship sank and the mirrors were
shattered by the water pressure, Joscar!

94
00:09:33.510 --> 00:09:36.700
Yeah, I guess that's it, Mascar!

95
00:09:36.700 --> 00:09:39.680
Something seems off about this...

96
00:09:41.190 --> 00:09:43.280
Hey, Luffy!

97
00:09:45.430 --> 00:09:46.390
Are you all right?!

98
00:09:46.720 --> 00:09:47.460
Chopper!

99
00:09:50.240 --> 00:09:53.700
I have something to tell you, so get away from the enemies!

100
00:09:53.700 --> 00:09:54.400
Okay!

101
00:09:56.340 --> 00:09:58.810
Are you guys all right?!

102
00:09:59.200 --> 00:10:02.170
Hey! Straw Hat is running away!

103
00:10:07.520 --> 00:10:11.740
What happened?!
The candy guy said the Sunny sank!

104
00:10:11.740 --> 00:10:16.530
We thought we were going to sink, too!
But Jinbe did something amazing!

105
00:10:21.830 --> 00:10:23.970
We're all fine, Luffy!

106
00:10:24.760 --> 00:10:28.220
Luffy-san!
We broke all the mirrors on the ship!

107
00:10:28.220 --> 00:10:30.180
I see! Good job!

108
00:10:30.180 --> 00:10:34.740
With this, our enemies won't be able to come here, but you won't be able to come back either!

109
00:10:34.740 --> 00:10:38.440
Yeah, that's okay!
I'll figure out someth–

110
00:10:38.440 --> 00:10:41.570
No you won't!
You don't even have a plan!

111
00:10:41.570 --> 00:10:43.320
Listen carefully, Luffy!

112
00:10:47.650 --> 00:10:51.620
Sanji-kun is baking the cake
on Cacao Island right now!

113
00:10:52.510 --> 00:10:54.940
That's where we're heading!

114
00:10:54.950 --> 00:10:58.040
At the earliest, we'll arrive in 10 hours!

115
00:10:58.040 --> 00:11:00.410
That's around one a.m.!

116
00:11:00.410 --> 00:11:03.750
So after you beat that guy up,

117
00:11:03.750 --> 00:11:08.380
search for a mirror that leads to Cacao Island!
We'll meet you there!

118
00:11:12.720 --> 00:11:15.540
Damn! I can't get it off!

119
00:11:20.240 --> 00:11:22.080
Is something wrong, Luffy?

120
00:11:22.080 --> 00:11:23.570
Can you hear me?

121
00:11:40.680 --> 00:11:41.750
Luffy!

122
00:11:41.750 --> 00:11:42.960
Yeah!

123
00:11:42.960 --> 00:11:44.900
Hey! Stay focused!

124
00:12:17.190 --> 00:12:19.200
Maybe he's in trouble!

125
00:12:19.200 --> 00:12:20.330
Please respond!

126
00:12:20.330 --> 00:12:21.820
Luffy!

127
00:12:23.290 --> 00:12:25.370
Are you okay, Luffy?!

128
00:12:25.370 --> 00:12:26.580
Luffy-san!

129
00:12:55.070 --> 00:12:56.320
Willow Mochi!

130
00:13:35.620 --> 00:13:37.210
Luffy?

131
00:13:37.210 --> 00:13:39.390
You're fine, right, Luffy-san?!

132
00:13:39.780 --> 00:13:42.620
What's the matter, Luffy?!

133
00:14:24.810 --> 00:14:26.980
Hurry up and get there, guys!

134
00:14:28.120 --> 00:14:31.870
I'll probably be there soon,
and I'll be tired of waiting!

135
00:14:33.720 --> 00:14:35.540
Yeah!

136
00:14:35.540 --> 00:14:37.870
See you later, guys!

137
00:14:37.870 --> 00:14:39.690
Yeah!

138
00:14:40.550 --> 00:14:44.230
Our pursuers will be here soon!
Let's keep an eye out!

139
00:14:44.230 --> 00:14:45.390
Roger!

140
00:14:45.390 --> 00:14:48.140
Let's go to the observation deck, Carrot!

141
00:14:48.140 --> 00:14:50.430
Okay, Chobro!

142
00:15:19.940 --> 00:15:22.710
"I don't plan on dying in a place like this,"

143
00:15:22.710 --> 00:15:24.630
is what you'll say next.

144
00:15:27.070 --> 00:15:29.480
Are those really your last words?

145
00:15:52.830 --> 00:15:56.540
I don't plan on dying in a place like this!

146
00:15:57.560 --> 00:16:01.500
No one dies because they want to.

147
00:16:02.590 --> 00:16:03.920
Most people...

148
00:16:04.520 --> 00:16:06.120
die against their will.

149
00:16:10.810 --> 00:16:12.140
He's right!

150
00:16:12.140 --> 00:16:14.980
Why don't you
drop dead already, Straw Hat?!

151
00:16:15.620 --> 00:16:16.440
Branch!

152
00:16:16.440 --> 00:16:18.370
The name's Brûlée!

153
00:16:18.370 --> 00:16:21.950
Don't think that you can beat him
with just your spirit, brat!

154
00:16:22.460 --> 00:16:26.870
Big Brother Katakuri
isn't just an undefeated man,

155
00:16:26.870 --> 00:16:33.520
he's a superhuman whose back has never once
touched the ground since he was born!

156
00:16:33.520 --> 00:16:35.000
Stop it, Brûlée!

157
00:16:35.850 --> 00:16:39.390
The legend goes like this:
The moment he was born,

158
00:16:39.390 --> 00:16:43.090
he stood up on his feet
and sat on a chair to sleep on it.

159
00:16:43.090 --> 00:16:49.060
He's never laid down in his life!
He's a man who scorns even the ground!

160
00:16:50.240 --> 00:16:51.910
He's always dignified...

161
00:16:51.910 --> 00:16:54.190
calm, and strong!

162
00:16:54.190 --> 00:16:56.700
He's the perfect human!

163
00:16:57.440 --> 00:17:02.260
That's our big brother, Katakuri!

164
00:17:03.220 --> 00:17:05.730
He's the Charlotte family's
greatest creation!

165
00:17:05.730 --> 00:17:09.080
So a small fry like you
challenging him to a duel

166
00:17:09.080 --> 00:17:12.300
is just absurd!

167
00:17:12.300 --> 00:17:14.810
Shut up! Go away!

168
00:17:22.050 --> 00:17:25.130
What are you trying to do...
to my little sister?!

169
00:17:26.670 --> 00:17:28.320
Big Brother!

170
00:17:48.840 --> 00:17:50.280
Mochi Thrust!

171
00:18:01.180 --> 00:18:02.470
Ouch...

172
00:18:07.000 --> 00:18:08.730
That was close!

173
00:18:22.810 --> 00:18:24.710
I almost got crushed!

174
00:18:30.320 --> 00:18:33.180
The name of this spear is Mogura!

175
00:18:37.160 --> 00:18:42.440
Your arms... or your legs?
Which body part do you want removed first?

176
00:18:43.750 --> 00:18:45.570
I'll sever them for you!

177
00:18:49.750 --> 00:18:52.650
Please start with his head, Big Bro!

178
00:18:52.650 --> 00:18:54.360
Shut up, already!

179
00:19:10.650 --> 00:19:12.950
Gum-Gum...

180
00:19:12.950 --> 00:19:15.920
Giant Rifle!

181
00:19:29.830 --> 00:19:31.690
I was listening!

182
00:19:31.690 --> 00:19:33.630
Straw Hat!

183
00:19:34.340 --> 00:19:37.410
I know about your meeting place.

184
00:19:38.370 --> 00:19:42.320
Do you wanna play
with a wave again, Mama?

185
00:19:42.400 --> 00:19:47.530
At Sea
Within the Territory

186
00:19:42.570 --> 00:19:45.120
Come on! Let's do it!

187
00:19:45.120 --> 00:19:47.530
Mama, are you listening?

188
00:19:48.120 --> 00:19:52.120
What?! Their ship hasn't sunk yet?!

189
00:19:52.120 --> 00:19:53.750
Are you sure, Brûlée?!

190
00:19:53.750 --> 00:19:56.490
Yes, I heard their voices!

191
00:19:56.520 --> 00:20:01.720
But my candy monster
swallowed them with a giant wave!

192
00:20:01.720 --> 00:20:04.240
How did they escape?!

193
00:20:06.950 --> 00:20:09.340
I don't know how they did it!

194
00:20:09.340 --> 00:20:15.500
But they're definitely still alive! They'll be showing up
on Cacao Island sometime tonight.

195
00:20:15.510 --> 00:20:20.220
That is what they promised Straw Hat Luffy.
There's no mistake!

196
00:20:20.220 --> 00:20:22.350
What they don't know is

197
00:20:22.360 --> 00:20:26.030
that it's our final destination, too!

198
00:20:27.160 --> 00:20:32.380
Mama! The cake you desire is
at Chocolat Town on Cacao Island!

199
00:20:32.380 --> 00:20:34.320
Aren't you excited?

200
00:20:34.800 --> 00:20:37.770
I lied to her out of desperation,

201
00:20:38.060 --> 00:20:43.370
but if I take Mama there like this,
I can cover up my lie!

202
00:20:43.370 --> 00:20:48.220
Pudding is baking the cake on Cacao Island!

203
00:20:48.890 --> 00:20:53.370
No matter what happens,
everything will be settled!

204
00:21:03.850 --> 00:21:07.560
Wedding cake!

205
00:21:07.560 --> 00:21:10.150
Mama, it's that way, huh?!

206
00:21:14.200 --> 00:21:18.660
Wait a sec! That's Nuts Island!

207
00:21:19.010 --> 00:21:21.510
Hey, hey, what are you doing?!

208
00:21:21.510 --> 00:21:26.630
Mama! Their ship didn't go that way!
The cake is on Cacao Island!

209
00:21:26.630 --> 00:21:31.420
Wedding cake!

210
00:21:28.540 --> 00:21:31.420
No, Mama! Stop!

211
00:21:31.420 --> 00:21:34.270
Don't go that way!

212
00:21:34.810 --> 00:21:36.860
Mirro-world

213
00:21:40.330 --> 00:21:41.980
He never learns!

214
00:21:43.040 --> 00:21:45.070
You bastard!

215
00:21:50.070 --> 00:21:52.150
Gum-Gum...

216
00:21:53.410 --> 00:21:57.460
Grizzly Corkscrew Magnum!

217
00:22:51.070 --> 00:22:52.140
Damn!

218
00:22:52.140 --> 00:22:55.520
He's always able to hit me when I dodge!

219
00:22:56.710 --> 00:22:58.540
That tires me out even more!

220
00:23:01.390 --> 00:23:02.750
It's the same for me.

221
00:23:04.040 --> 00:23:07.450
Nobody has ever
dodged my attacks like you have.

222
00:23:08.020 --> 00:23:09.210
It's stressful!

223
00:23:25.740 --> 00:23:28.270
You tried to take Mogura away from me...

224
00:23:30.080 --> 00:23:32.900
Damn! I almost got it!

225
00:23:34.570 --> 00:23:35.910
Flowing Mochi!

226
00:23:50.430 --> 00:23:53.640
Wha...?! What's this?!

227
00:23:55.320 --> 00:23:57.270
The ground became mochi !

228
00:24:03.660 --> 00:24:06.360
This is just like what Doflamingo did!

229
00:24:08.080 --> 00:24:10.410
Listen up, fledgling!

230
00:24:12.670 --> 00:24:20.510
Devil fruit abilities have
yet another stage to them, called "awakening"!

231
00:24:21.410 --> 00:24:24.510
Of course my ability is awakened.

232
00:24:30.760 --> 00:24:31.960
Oh, no!

233
00:24:31.960 --> 00:24:33.730
It's no use.

234
00:24:33.730 --> 00:24:37.010
With your elasticity and viscosity,
you can't move anymore.

235
00:24:41.320 --> 00:24:43.680
Should I just chop you up?

236
00:24:44.000 --> 00:24:47.320
Or should I let you suffocate in the mochi ?

237
00:24:47.320 --> 00:24:49.560
How would you like to die?

238
00:24:49.560 --> 00:24:51.840
I'm not gonna die!

239
00:24:54.980 --> 00:24:56.750
Gear Fourth?

240
00:24:58.000 --> 00:24:59.710
How interesting.

241
00:25:02.570 --> 00:25:06.590
Whole Cake Island (Sweet City)

242
00:25:11.100 --> 00:25:12.430
How odd...

243
00:25:14.680 --> 00:25:18.820
We haven't gotten a report
on the location of the Straw Hats' ship.

244
00:25:18.820 --> 00:25:21.640
What are the territorial sea slugs doing?!

245
00:25:23.280 --> 00:25:25.060
Shut up, Pekoms!

246
00:25:25.060 --> 00:25:27.350
Just stop crying already!

247
00:25:28.580 --> 00:25:31.530
Big Bro Pedro!

248
00:25:33.460 --> 00:25:35.070
I feel pity for him...

249
00:25:35.070 --> 00:25:37.000
It's hard to believe that your

250
00:25:37.000 --> 00:25:40.750
childhood friend and big brother
chose to die by suicide bombing-bon...

251
00:25:40.750 --> 00:25:42.000
He was our enemy!

252
00:25:42.460 --> 00:25:43.420
Bon...

253
00:25:45.130 --> 00:25:49.600
It's pointless to die here!
The day of the new dawn is coming!

254
00:25:50.100 --> 00:25:52.010
I must go back to my country!

255
00:25:54.060 --> 00:25:57.430
This will break all
of your magic spells, right?

256
00:25:58.310 --> 00:25:59.350
Bombs?!

257
00:26:00.400 --> 00:26:01.520
Farewell.

258
00:26:10.080 --> 00:26:13.530
It was a shock to me as well-amour...

259
00:26:16.040 --> 00:26:23.410
Five years ago, I witnessed Pedro begging for his life, tears and all-bon.

260
00:26:23.410 --> 00:26:29.370
And that same man sacrificed his life
to allow them to sail away!

261
00:26:29.370 --> 00:26:30.630
Who cares?

262
00:26:34.430 --> 00:26:36.050
Big Bro...

263
00:26:36.850 --> 00:26:43.770
We may still be underestimating
Straw Hat Luffy-issant !

264
00:26:43.770 --> 00:26:45.260
What's your point?

265
00:26:45.260 --> 00:26:48.510
My point is that we should
take this more seriously-bon !

266
00:26:48.510 --> 00:26:51.460
Mama will never be taken out
by a brat like him!

267
00:26:51.460 --> 00:26:55.040
Are you saying that Straw Hat Luffy
is that much weaker than her?

268
00:26:55.040 --> 00:26:58.160
Of course!
As a pirate, she's in a different class!

269
00:26:59.290 --> 00:27:03.750
Can you say the same even while
looking at Mama's fallen castle?!

270
00:27:03.750 --> 00:27:05.750
That happened by chance!

271
00:27:05.750 --> 00:27:12.350
An accident you say?! And are the sea slugs
neglecting their security duties by chance as well?!

272
00:27:13.420 --> 00:27:18.080
What?! Are you telling me that
all of this is part of their plan as well?!

273
00:27:18.080 --> 00:27:19.900
At the very least,

274
00:27:19.900 --> 00:27:24.730
since the Straw Hats arrived, unexpected incidents have occurred one after the other-jour !

275
00:27:28.520 --> 00:27:32.410
Arrogant rulers will have the rug
pulled out from under them.

276
00:27:32.410 --> 00:27:35.740
To prevent the one-in-a-million chance
that Mama's name is tarnished,

277
00:27:35.740 --> 00:27:41.880
a powerful fleet should be sent to the border
of our territory as the final line of defense-amour !

278
00:27:55.110 --> 00:27:56.300
Minister Mont d'Or.

279
00:27:56.300 --> 00:27:57.060
What?

280
00:27:57.060 --> 00:27:59.690
There's a call from Minister Custard
on the transponder snail.

281
00:27:59.690 --> 00:28:02.790
Custard was chasing after Bege, wasn't she?

282
00:28:03.650 --> 00:28:07.620
This is Mont d'Or.
Did you take care of Bege?

283
00:28:07.620 --> 00:28:08.620
Well...

284
00:28:10.780 --> 00:28:13.680
We lost track of his ship.

285
00:28:13.680 --> 00:28:14.870
What?!

286
00:28:14.870 --> 00:28:18.840
The territorial sea slugs aren't sending us
the location of the ship!

287
00:28:18.840 --> 00:28:21.000
Huh?! It's not just us?!

288
00:28:21.000 --> 00:28:21.520
What?!

289
00:28:21.520 --> 00:28:25.760
We haven't gotten the location
of the Straw Hats, either!

290
00:28:25.760 --> 00:28:27.090
Are you serious?!

291
00:28:27.090 --> 00:28:32.970
In any case, look for Bege!
Listen! Don't let him get away, no matter what!

292
00:28:32.970 --> 00:28:33.930
I understand!

293
00:28:35.330 --> 00:28:37.750
Hey! Check on them right away!

294
00:28:37.750 --> 00:28:38.440
What?

295
00:28:38.440 --> 00:28:42.380
I'm telling you to check up
on the territorial sea slugs on the sea floor!

296
00:28:42.380 --> 00:28:43.030
Yes, sir!

297
00:28:43.030 --> 00:28:46.570
What the hell is happening down there?!

298
00:28:46.820 --> 00:28:51.500
Nostra Castello: "Our Castle" in Italian
The Nostra Castello
At Sea

299
00:28:51.500 --> 00:28:54.960
I was expecting more of them to chase us!

300
00:28:54.960 --> 00:28:56.720
What's going on?

301
00:28:56.720 --> 00:29:00.770
Maybe they're not tracking our location-rero.

302
00:29:00.770 --> 00:29:02.420
The territorial sea slugs?

303
00:29:02.420 --> 00:29:03.810
Rero.

304
00:29:03.810 --> 00:29:08.860
If there are territorial sea slugs,
then the transponder snails should react.

305
00:29:08.860 --> 00:29:10.890
But they're silent-rero.

306
00:29:10.890 --> 00:29:14.870
I've never heard of anything like this!

307
00:29:15.200 --> 00:29:19.110
But that's great.
Keep it at maximum speed!

308
00:29:19.870 --> 00:29:22.280
Hurry to Cacao Island!

309
00:29:22.280 --> 00:29:26.360
Let's take the shortest route
to pick up Chiffon!

310
00:29:26.360 --> 00:29:30.280
– Yeah!
– Rero!

311
00:29:55.470 --> 00:29:58.460
This is Nusstorte, speaking from Germa's ship.
Nusstorte: "Engadiner Nusstorte", a Swiss nut tart

312
00:29:58.460 --> 00:30:01.070
Big Brother!
How did things go with Germa?!

313
00:30:01.070 --> 00:30:06.940
We crushed them with 10,000 soldiers.
Their kingdom has been devastated!

314
00:30:06.940 --> 00:30:07.830
Oh!

315
00:30:07.840 --> 00:30:11.290
As expected! But you shouldn't
go overboard like that...

316
00:30:11.290 --> 00:30:16.260
With our strength, it was a piece of cake...

317
00:30:16.260 --> 00:30:18.240
By the way, Big Brother...

318
00:30:19.070 --> 00:30:24.740
Kingdom of Germa

319
00:30:20.210 --> 00:30:24.740
You didn't destroy
their cloning system, did you?

320
00:30:25.420 --> 00:30:29.290
Of course not.
That's what we came here for.

321
00:30:29.290 --> 00:30:33.250
But other than that, the place has been
completely destroyed.

322
00:30:34.470 --> 00:30:36.290
That's the least we could do!

323
00:30:36.290 --> 00:30:40.630
Damn Germa! They were doomed
the moment we had them in our sights!

324
00:30:40.630 --> 00:30:43.270
What happened to the Straw Hats?

325
00:30:44.020 --> 00:30:47.550
Actually, we accidentally let them get away.

326
00:30:47.550 --> 00:30:50.170
They're heading due west...

327
00:30:51.030 --> 00:30:53.810
Well, it's only a matter
of time before we get them.

328
00:30:53.810 --> 00:30:56.490
I'll leave it to you!

329
00:30:56.490 --> 00:30:59.080
Yeah, good job!

330
00:31:00.620 --> 00:31:03.490
And that's how you do it...

331
00:31:04.170 --> 00:31:07.150
So Luffy-kun and the others are okay.

332
00:31:07.150 --> 00:31:10.300
What should we do now?

333
00:31:13.930 --> 00:31:16.430
Let's go! Set sail!

334
00:31:16.970 --> 00:31:18.670
Roger!

335
00:31:19.670 --> 00:31:21.980
Muscle Balloon!

336
00:31:40.020 --> 00:31:44.030
Why should I stand here and watch...

337
00:31:44.030 --> 00:31:46.570
when I already know
that you're going to power up?

338
00:31:56.990 --> 00:31:59.330
Hey, Straw Hat Luffy.

339
00:32:01.470 --> 00:32:02.880
I'll tell you this now...

340
00:32:03.580 --> 00:32:05.570
I'm not underestimating you!

341
00:32:17.650 --> 00:32:18.950
Mirror Mochi!

342
00:32:18.940 --> 00:32:21.510
What? That's mochi ?!

343
00:32:21.510 --> 00:32:24.980
This is bad! If I get crushed
under all that mochi, I'll be buried alive!

344
00:32:24.980 --> 00:32:27.150
Yes, you'll suffocate.

345
00:32:28.150 --> 00:32:29.610
This is where you die!

346
00:32:47.560 --> 00:32:53.400
I'm sorry that the fight has to end like this,
but it's made me a little irritated.

347
00:32:53.400 --> 00:32:56.030
Because you held on
for much longer than expected,

348
00:32:56.030 --> 00:32:59.360
I'm 40 minutes late for today's merienda.
Merienda: Spanish word for a light meal

349
00:33:03.910 --> 00:33:05.290
The suffering won't last long...

350
00:33:08.490 --> 00:33:10.670
Farewell, Straw Hat...
